messages.content:
Your job is to search google calendar for avaialbility to book a customer in. 

You receive a date from the customer, you must output a JSON object in the format of {"start-date": "start date for search", "end-date": "end date for search"}. 

For Example, if you receive, November 25th 9 PM, your output will be {"start-date": "2024-11-25", "end-date": "2024-11-26"}.

Proposed date: {{1.message}}

Note, current date is: {{15.currentTime}}

messages.content:
You receive a proposed time to book a client meeting, and you also receive "busy" information from the calendar on the day. Your job is to out "Accept" if the proposed time doesn't clash with busy time, and output "Deny" if the proposed time clashes with busy time.

Note, For example, if the proposed time starts at 10am, and another meeting finishes at 10am, the proposed time is acceptable.

Proposed time: {{1.message}} Melbourne AU Time.

Busy times: {{24.json}} (in UTC time, note that you need to convert to Melbourne AU time to complete your task).

messages.content:
You just tried to book someone in for a meeting but the slot they wanted was not free. You receive information of the slot they wanted, and also busy times for that day. Your job is to suggest a new time slot for the meeting that does not coincide with already busy times. E.g., "Friday 27th November at 2PM" 

Note, For example, if the proposed time starts at 10am, and another meeting finishes at 10am, the proposed time is acceptable.

Proposed time by client: {{1.message}} (in Melbourne AU time)

Busy times: {{24.json}} (in UTC time, note that you need to convert to Melbourne AU time to complete your task).

messages.content:
You receive an input of a proposed time slot and a revised time slot. 

The proposed time slot was the customers proposed time, but we can't accept it as we already have booking. The revised time slot is a free slot we can offer to the customer. 

Convert this into a JSON output in the following format {"rebook": "string:}. 

Example output for input of proposed slot Friday 27th November 9AM and revised time slow of Friday 27th November 3PM - output {"rebook": "Sorry, Friday 27th November at 9AM isn't available, but we can do 3PM instead, does this work for you?"}
